image_desc: Photo shared by Jiezhen on December 29, 2020 tagging @jaredkonggg, @jiezhen, @christine_anne_kong, and @bernardkongyoon. May be an image of 6 people, people standing and food.
text:
Our first week out of our 14-day #SHN quarantine was filled with our top three priorities for this trip: family, friends and food. It was also timely that I took my annual holiday digital detox - spending most of my time disconnecting from my devices to reconnect with those around me. While our hearts and bellies are so full from the last week, it did take some time for @jaredkonggg and me to adjust to being around so many people and feeling safe - seeing that weâ€™ve spent the majority of this pandemic isolated at home and seeing the same 6 people. 
.
The holidays also felt so different this year - it was the first Christmas in my entire life that my family has spent apart (with @jiemingg in Europe and @shang285 in the US), and I know so many who are also spending the holidays away from their loved ones this year. And while Singapore has been somewhat of bubble, a reprieve away from Covid for a little while, we know we will be heading back to California soon - and are just soaking in this slice of normalcy as best we can while weâ€™re here. 
.
And as we wrap up the last days of the year that 2020 has been, I hope we all manage to find some hope, love and light, wherever we may be. Sending you and your loved ones so much love as we transition into the new year and lay this year to rest.
.
The next few days for me are often a time of reflection, introspection and setting intentions for the coming year. Am looking forward to seeing what emerges for us all in the new year ğŸ’™ğŸŒŸğŸ€
.

The past 10 days had gone by without me realizing it. I've brought along my threads and art stuffs to keep myself occupied among other things but ended up doing almost none of them.
.
So I decided this cannot be, I have to make something. Took out a cross stitch bookmark kit I had kept for ages. The original design given is a flower but I decided to change it to a simple kufic khat design.
.
The little OCD in me is screaming, "It is not in the center!" but I can't do much as the number of count is odd. I guess I just have to make do with the final outcome and be satisfied that I even finished this at all. Heh.
.
5 more days to FREEDOMMMM!
.
.

text:
The Sunday Times @straits_times â€” todayâ€™s column explores my travels home to ğŸ‡ºğŸ‡¸ and the return to SHN in ğŸ‡¸ğŸ‡¬
.

â€œTwas two days post-Christmas, and all through our home, every creature is stirring, quarantine no longer confining our zone. Predictable sunny skies beam over our heads, yet we dream of a Singapore day with a white whisper of snowfall instead. 
A stroll down Orchard Road has masks covering every face, as we live in fear of the pandemicâ€™s rapid pace. Teens dressed for the tropics in tank tops and flip flops watch as anxious parents vent, non-stop, as the frightful virus leaves us in a genuine kerfuffle, muddling up our holiday shuffle.â€

The rhyme ends here as the main point of the column unfolds, but I enjoyed this little jingle. ğŸ¥°
.

.
.
.

image_desc:
We are on our 7th day of SHN at the hotel now. So far the stay at the hotel has been nothing but great. However if there is any downside, there is no housekeeping so the rooms tend to get somewhat dusty.

As the windows are shut right & we also eat in the same room, there will tend to be the built up of smell. 

Thankfully I brought back 2 diffusers (YL diffusers are dual voltage) & we have been diffusing ğ—£ğ—¨ğ—¥ğ—œğ—™ğ—œğ—–ğ ğ—§ğ—œğğ—¡  on a daily basis.

image_desc: Photo shared by Jiezhen on December 16, 2020 tagging @copthornekings. May be an image of coffee cup.
text: #SHN Quarantine Update ğŸŒ± We havenâ€™t stepped out of this room for 9 days - and while there have been moments where we feel like weâ€™re in a bubble, it hasnâ€™t been too bad. I suppose my self-imposed isolation and lockdown in Boston earlier this year (when I didnâ€™t leave my apartment building for a month) was good practice for this 14-day mandatory Stay-Home Notice (SHN) that all travelers into Singapore must undergo. And even though I do miss our daily walks outside, this time of rest and stillness has also been much needed after the whirlwind that 2020 has been. Our stay is completely paid for by the Singapore government , where we receive 3 warm meals a day (and sometimes more thanks to our friends and family dropping off treats), and have been getting lots of rest and finding our rhythms and routines that have allowed us to thrive in these times. So in between the quiet mornings, food deliveries, candlelit dinner dates, creative work setups, distanced visits from family and friends (where they wave to us from the parking lot), @soupstories, ukulele playtime, yoga/workouts, sangha and meditation sessions and taking in the Singapore skyline from our little balcony, weâ€™ve been embracing this time of transition where we have nowhere to go, nowhere to rush to, and just to embrace the present moment we are in. Super grateful to the staff at @copthornekings who have been taking really good care of us (and even providing extra vegetables for Lucky Charm) and to @stb_sg for managing the enormity of the SHN operations and taking care of the many Singaporeans and residents who are coming home - I can only imagine what it takes to make this possible. Feeling a heart full of gratitude as we enter this festive season, knowing that it might look a little different this year but also feeling so thankful to the many everyday heroes around the world who have worked behind the scenes to keep communities safe during this time. We are able to stand here because of you. It is my hope that in this festive season that lies ahead, that we take a moment to acknowledge all the love that is around, even if it feels different this year. â¤ï¸ğŸŒŸğŸ„ #celebratingloveinthetimeofcorona #quarantine
location: Copthorne King's Hotel Singapore on Havelock

image_desc: Photo by Cavvy Chin on December 16, 2020. May be an image of 3 people.
text:
14 day Stay-Home Notice (SHN).
#shn #quarantine

#SHN #DAILY saying thank u to all the #guests that appeared on #Soulful #House #Nation this year. Also, #thank #u to the #people behind the #scene and the #viewers  who helped us have a #successful year. Weâ€™re taking a #break til #next #year when we come back with more #great #guests and #new #segments. Plz #watch, #like,#comment, #TAG 3 #PEOPLE AND #SHARE!!!

During Covid situation, I am unexpectedly being granted a Spore PR. After a long administration process, finally I can enter the border and reunited with hubby. Spore border is not open yet, after getting the approval, I need to undergo 14 days QuarantineğŸ˜± in Spore dedicated facilities, which are 4&5 Star Luxury Hotels. 

Yes, it is a luxury hotel, but.. I realized that Freedom is more luxury! Bored, emotions fluctuation, 14days just stay in the room alone, can't go even a step out. Such a Life experience ever! I would like to share this life experience at the same time start learning making a video,  #shn #karantina #lifeexperience

Support my newborn YouTube channel for more Life Experience video, that you may get some insights from, Enjoy! ğŸ˜†

https://youtube.com/channel/UCtpvj_Zr34_klSR3ovncVZw

So much love has been poured into this track & I really hope you guys enjoy it, dance to it, sing in the shower to it, share it with your friends, family & enemies, add it into your party playlists and just overall make it your own.
